    },
    {
      "id": "two-phase-api",
      "title": "The Two-Phase API",
      "description": "Pretext splits work into two phases. The prepare phase does expensive one-time segmenting, measuring, and caching, returning an opaque handle. The layout phase then uses only cached arithmetic — safe to call thousands of times per frame. A richer variant also exposes segment arrays and bidi levels for custom rendering.",
      "focusDirectory": "src",
      "colorMode": "fileTypes",
      "highlightLayers": [
        {
