      "id": "browser-accuracy",
      "title": "Browser Accuracy Infrastructure",
      "description": "Pretext is validated against real browser layout in Chrome, Safari, and Firefox — currently perfect across all three. The accuracy sweep renders text in both the DOM and Pretext, comparing line breaks at every combination of 4 fonts, 8 sizes, 8 widths, and 30 texts. Checked-in snapshots serve as regression gates. The diagnostic tools include a probe page for isolating individual snippets and a corpus viewer for deep-diving into mismatches.",
